 opsys←os _opsys
    ⍝ What OS are we running on?
    :Select ⊢_opsys←3↑⊃'.'⎕WG'APLversion'
    :Case 'AIX'
        opsys←'AIX'

    :Case 'Mac'
        opsys←'MacOS'

    :Case 'Win'
        opsys←'Windows'

    :Case 'Lin'
        ⍝ Further differentiate a Linux system
        ⍝ TODO: Find a way to implement the 'uname'-provided functionality in APL.
        :Select 4↑⊃⎕SH'uname -a'
        :Case 'armv'
            ⍝ Assume 'armv' to be RaspberryPI
            opsys←'RaspberryPi'

        :Else
            ⍝ Linux in general otherwise
            ⍝ Returns the '<OS>-<Compiler-Suite>' combination (in most cases: 'linux-gnu')
            ⍝ TODO: At very least, perform the corresponding 'tr' + 'sed' functionality in APL.
            opsys←⎕SH'uname -o |tr "A-Z" "a-z" |sed -E ''s!([^/]+)/(.+)$!\2-\1!'''
        :EndSelect

    :Else
        ('Unknown operating system: ',_opsys)⎕SIGNAL 11
 :EndSelect
